hedline.hl1: World Business Briefing | Europe: Switzerland: W.T.O. Still Snagged On China

abstract.p: Negotiators trying to put final touches on China's entry into World Trade Organization appear to be stymied by some last-minute problems, including conditions that will govern expansion of American International Group (S)

block.p: Negotiators trying to put the final touches on China's entry into the World Trade Organization appeared to be stymied by some last-minute problems, including the conditions that will govern the expansion of American International Group, the insurance company. Envoys insisted they could meet tomorrow's deadline to usher in one of the organization's biggest members. Among the remaining differences were exactly what goods China wanted on its list of those subject to price controls.
